findStrings.find: /** * Created by 1 on 21.09.2017. */ public class Knapsack { public int max(int a, int b) { return (a > b) ? a : b; } public int solution(int[] v, int[] w, int W, int n) { int K[][] = new int[n + 1][W + 1]; for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) { for (int j = 0; j <= W; j++) { if (i == 0 || j == 0) { K[i][j] = 0; } if (w[i - 1] <= W) { K[i][j]=max(K[i - 1][j], K[i - 1][j - w[i-1] + v[i]]); } else { K[i][j] = K[i - 1][j]; } } } return K[n][W]; } public static void main(String args[]) { int[] val = new int[]{10, 10, 100}; int[] w = new int[]{1, 2, 3}; int W = 10; int n = val.length; Knapsack k = new Knapsack(); k.solution(val, w, W, n); } }
